<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-541-539  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 541 539.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Communications of the ACM  Oct 1990 v33 n10 pS8(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Association for Computing Machinery 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Additions to History Series books. (History Series of the ACMPress) (Pubs Corner) (ACMemberNet supplement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT/><NOTE>Only Text is presented here; see printed issues for graphics.andO;</NOTE><TEXT>Additions to History Series Books Two recent additions to the History Seriesof the ACM Press Books program provide enticing historical insight into twovery different aspects of computing.andM;The first, A History of Medical Informatics, edited by Bruce I. Blum of theApplied Physics Laboratory at the Johns Hopkins University and Karen Duncanof Health Information Systems, takes a first-hand look at the earlydevelopment of medical informatics--the application of computer technology tomedicine.andM;The second book, A History of Scientific Computing, illustrates how theinvention of the computer profoundly affected both the way computations areperformed and the overall course of modern science and mathematics.andP;  Thesefascinating stories are told from the unique perspective of the doctors,scientists, and mathematicians who contributed to the advancement of thesefields.andO;</TEXT></DOC>